---
const pageTitle = "About Me";
const identity = {
  firstName: "Sarah",
  country: "Connecticut",
  occupation: "Software Engineer",
  hobbies: ["coding", "reading", "soup brewing"],
};

const skills = ["HTML", "CSS", "JavaScript", "Python", "C", "Roadmap Planning"];

const happy = true;
const finished = false;
const goal = 3;
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <p>Here are a few facts about me:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>My name is {identity.firstName}.</li>
        <li>I live in {identity.country} and work as a {identity.occupation}.</li>
        {identity.hobbies.length >= 2 &&
            <li>Two of my hobbies are: {identity.hobbies[0]} and {identity.hobbies[1]}</li>
        }
    </ul>
    <p>My skills are:</p>
    <ul>
  {skills.map((skill) => <li>{skill}</li>)}
  {happy && <p>I am happy to be learning Astro!</p>}

{finished && <p>I finished this tutorial!</p>}

{goal === 3 ? <p>My goal is to finish in 3 days.</p> : <p>My goal is not 3 days.</p>}
</ul>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=VT323&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'VT323', monospace;
            background-color: #00008B; /* Dark Blue */
            color: #00FF00; /* Neon Green */
            background-image: url('https://www.transparenttextures.com/patterns/stardust.png');
            line-height: 1.8;
            margin: 2em;
            padding: 1em;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
        }
        h1, h2, h3 {
            color: #FF00FF; /* Hot Pink */
            text-shadow: 2px 2px #00FFFF; /* Cyan */
        }
        .container {
            border: 4px dotted #FFFF00; /* Yellow */
            padding: 1em;
            margin-bottom: 2em;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
        }
        .container img {
            border: 4px solid #FF00FF;
            border-radius: 0;
            width: 150px;
            height: 150px;
            image-rendering: pixelated;
            margin-right: 2em;
        }
        .content {
            flex: 1;
        }
        .journey-section {
            margin-top: 3em;
        }
        .journey-item {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            margin-bottom: 2em;
            background-color: #333333;
            padding: 1em;
            border: 2px dashed #00FF00;
        }
        .journey-item img {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            margin-right: 1.5em;
            border: none;
            image-rendering: pixelated;
        }
        a {
            color: #00FFFF;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
        a:hover {
            color: #FF00FF;
        }
        .visitor-counter {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 3em;
        }
        .visitor-counter img {
            width: 150px;
        }
        nav {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 2em;
        }
        nav a {
            margin: 0 1em;
            font-size: 1.5em;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <nav>
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/about/">About</a>
        <a href="/blog/">Blog</a>
    </nav>
    <div class="container">
        <img src="https://placehold.co/150x150/1E40AF/FFFFFF/png?text=Me" alt="Cartoon avatar of a computer science graduate">
        <div class="content">
            <h1>About Me</h1>
            <p>Penn State CS Graduate | Game Developer | Software Enthusiast</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p>
        Hello! I'm a proud alumn of Penn State University with a Bachelors degree in Computer Science. 
        For the past five years, I've been on an exciting adventure in the video game industry, 
        testing immersive worlds and advocating for players by developing tools for testers, 
        desgining test tools, creating test plans, and leading quality on multiple game features. 
        It was a fantastic journey, but my heart has always been in the problem solving and creativity of 
        software development. For that reason, I've decided to take a step back from quality to fully dedicate time to 
        developing and learning updated technology stacks.
    </p>
    <p>
        I'm now diving back into the broader world of software engineering, eager to apply my problem-solving skills and creativity to new challenges. My passion lies in building elegant, efficient, and user-friendly applications that solve real problems.
    </p>

    <div class="journey-section">
        <h2>My Journey</h2>
        <div class="journey-item">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/100x100/1E40AF/FFFFFF/png?text=PSU" alt="Cartoon of a graduation cap">
            <div>
                <h3>Penn State Roots</h3>
                <p>My foundational years at Penn State gave me a solid grasp of computer science principles, from algorithms to computer vision and everything in between. We are!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="journey-item">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/100x100/FFFFFF/000000/png?text=Games" alt="Cartoon of a game controller">
            <div>
                <h3>XBOX Adventure</h3>
                <p>For five years, I worked on several game titles, which honed my skills evaluating software for quality issues, developing test tools, and collaboratively planing to ensure quality projects stay on track
                    for high priority releases in a fast-paced environment.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="journey-item">
            <img src="https://placehold.co/100x100/000000/FFFFFF/png?text=Code" alt="Cartoon of code on a screen">
            <div>
                <h3>Back to Software</h3>
                <p>I'm excited to be back in the world of software development, working on projects and continuing to learn and grow as an engineer.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
   
</body>
</html>